===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|mōnandæġ||day of the moon}}, from {{m|ang|mōna||moon}} + {{term|dæg||day|lang=ang}}, late {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*mēniniz dagaz}}, a translation of Latin {{term|dies lunae|lang=la}}. Compare West Frisian {{term|moandei|lang=fy}}, Low German {{term|Maandag|lang=nds}}, {{term|Maondag|lang=nds}}, Dutch {{term|maandag|lang=nl}}, German {{term|Montag|lang=de}}, Danish {{term|mandag|lang=da}}.

